## LangGraph Pipeline — Node-by-Node Flow

```
┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────┐     ┌──────────┐     ┌────────────────┐
│   classify   │ ──→ │   agent  │ ──→ │  tools   │ ──→ │ collect_chunks │
│    node      │     │   node   │     │  (Tool)  │     │      node      │
└──────────────┘     └──────────┘     └──────────┘     └────────────────┘
       ↓                    ↓              ↓                        ↓
  Sets doc_type        LLM decides     Executes              Extracts chunks
  (sds/tds)           to call tool    retrieve_chunks       from responses
```

### Conditional Edge: `should_continue`

| Condition | Transition |
|-----------|------------|
| `iterations >= 5` | → END (safety cap) |
| `last_message.tool_calls` exists | → `tools` (call retrieval) |
| Otherwise | → `collect_chunks` (end loop) |

### State Flow

```python
GraphState = {
    "messages": Annotated[list[BaseMessage], operator.add],  # Accumulates
    "question": str,           # Raw user question
    "doc_type": str,          # "sds" or "tds"
    "chunks_retrieved": list, # Retrieved chunk dicts
    "tool_was_called": bool, # Did agent call tool?
    "iterations": int,       # Loop count
    "error": str | None,     # Error propagation
}
```

